1. Based on the possible responses given in the request, we interpreted this question as "1. Under Condition 1 and if the next hurricane season was identical to the last, how satisfied with the government would you be with the new aid allocation strategy? (choose one)". So this is their absolute satisfaction, not their satisfaction relative to the original conditions. If you would like the participants' relative satisfaction, submit another research request stipulating that it be given to the same pool of actors who responded to this research request.

7-13. Question 7 mentions a new shelter, but there's no new shelter in this intervention. So we were not sure how to interpret these items, although we suspect the question is merely what would the participants' responses be under the current aid strategy. If you wish to submit a research request that clarifies these items, you can stipulate that it be given to the same pool of actors who responded to this research request.
